<html lang="{{ site.lang }}">

<head>
  <title>{{ site.title }}</title>
  <meta name="description" content="Sample" />
  <meta name="keywords" content="sample, something" />
  <meta name="charset" content="UTF-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
  <meta name="theme-color" content="#FA7C23" />
  <link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="./index.css" />
</head>

<body>
  {{> pageMenu }}
  <div>
    <section class="main">
      <section class="page-header">
        <img class="tc39-box" src={logo} />
      </section>
      <span class="project-tagline">
        <h2>Specifying ECMAScript.</h2>
      </span>
      <section class="side-info">
        <span class="basic-info">
          <h3>Who?</h3>
          <p>
            The specification is standardized by the TC39 (Technical committee 39) of ECMA (European Computer Manufacturers Association).
            You can read our 
            <a href="https://ecma-international.org/memento/TC39.htm#Scope">
              the scope of our work here
            </a>
          </p>
        </span>
        <span class="basic-info">
          <h3>How?</h3>
          <p>
            We have a 
            <a href="https://tc39.github.io/process-document/">
              four stage process
            </a>  with a rolling release schedule with a new specification published every year.
          </p> 
          <p>
            Proposals move through stages at TC39 meetings, which are held every
            <a href="https://github.com/tc39/agendas/">two months</a>, and the
            <a href="https://github.com/tc39/tc39-notes/">Notes</a>  are made public.
          </p>
        </span>
        <span class="basic-info">
          <h3>Want to get involved?</h3>
          <p>
            There are many opportunities to get involved on an individual level. Check out our
            <a href="https://github.com/tc39/proposals/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md">
              Contributor Documentation
            </a>  and our guides to learn more. To get involved with the committee on an organizational level, read our
            <a href="https://ecma-international.org/memento/TC39-M.htm">
              Joining the TC39
            </a>  documentation.
          </p>
        </span>
      </section>
      <section class="main-content">{{{ page.content }}}</section>
      <section class="footer">
        <span class="footer-item">
          <a href="https://github.com/tc39/ecma262#ecmascript" class="btn menu-btn">
            Proposals
          </a>
        </span>
      </section>
    </section>
  </div>
</body>

</html>
